    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Was rather surprised to see that Cython requires the GIL to use things like `npy_isnan`. Given the function/macro is pure C, not really sure what good the GIL would do. Also would have figured the [`nogil` in `cdef extern`]( https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/0.27.3/Cython/Includes/numpy/math.pxd#L20 ) would have ensured that all functions in that block did not require the GIL. Regardless it appears to be needed. Here is a test file demonstrating the problem below and the compilation error.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Test file</summary>\r\n\r\n```cython\r\n#filename: test.pyx\r\n\r\ncimport numpy\r\ncimport numpy.math\r\n\r\ncdef bint test(double a) nogil:\r\n    return numpy.math.npy_isnan(a)\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nUsing version\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Compilation error</summary>\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cython --version\r\nCython version 0.27.3\r\n\r\n$ cython test.pyx\r\n\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\ncimport numpy\r\ncimport numpy.math\r\n\r\ncdef bint test(double a) nogil:\r\n    return numpy.math.npy_isnan(a)\r\n                    ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ntest.pyx:5:21: cimported module has no attribute 'npy_isnan'\r\n\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\ncimport numpy\r\ncimport numpy.math\r\n\r\ncdef bint test(double a) nogil:\r\n    return numpy.math.npy_isnan(a)\r\n                              ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ntest.pyx:5:31: Calling gil-requiring function not allowed without gil\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>",
    "closed_at": "2017-11-10T07:29:27Z",
